Description: p2-read-dotenv — point skills at ~/.obsidian-wiki/config
 Audit p2 (docs/260418-dual-sensitivity-analysis.md §5.3) flags 12
 locations across the vendor tree that tell skills to "Read `.env` to
 get `OBSIDIAN_VAULT_PATH`". This is misleading : the actual CLAUDE.md
 contract (and the `wiki-update` / `wiki-query` cross-project skills)
 already reads `~/.obsidian-wiki/config` FIRST, and only falls back to
 `.env` inside the repo as a secondary source.
 .
 Severity : TROMPEUR (misleading but not blocking — skills still work,
 but their documented startup sequence lies about the precedence).
 .
 This patch rewrites every occurrence to the truthful wording :
 "Read `~/.obsidian-wiki/config` (preferred) or `.env` (fallback) ..."
 while preserving the specific variable lists that follow (each file
 lists slightly different vars — CLAUDE_HISTORY_PATH, CODEX_HISTORY_PATH,
 OBSIDIAN_SOURCES_DIR, etc.).
 .
 Targets (12) :
   - .skills/wiki-status/SKILL.md
   - .skills/wiki-lint/SKILL.md
   - .skills/cross-linker/SKILL.md
   - .skills/tag-taxonomy/SKILL.md
   - .skills/wiki-rebuild/SKILL.md
   - .skills/wiki-export/SKILL.md
   - .skills/data-ingest/SKILL.md
   - .skills/claude-history-ingest/SKILL.md
   - .skills/codex-history-ingest/SKILL.md
   - .cursor/rules/obsidian-wiki.mdc
   - .windsurf/rules/obsidian-wiki.md
   - .github/copilot-instructions.md
 .
 Design §5.1 granularity : one thematic change → one patch, even when
 multi-file. Applying this as 12 separate patches would create noise
 with no gain.
